Asset Generator Web Interface  Company : Sartorius  Team Size : 3  Role : Lead developer  Technology used : React, .NET Core, C#, MongoDB, Azure App Service  Duration : September 2022 - Present  Synopsis :   This is a .NET Core based application for porting an existing Windows Forms application to a Web Interface. The application is hosted on an Azure App Service plan using React for the front end, .NET Core Web API for the backend and MongoDB as the database.    Responsibilities :   Understanding the legacy desktop codebase and creating the user stories for translating the various modules to a web based interface.  Co-ordinating with various teams in Germany, UK and India  Application development lead in India  Assigning and reviewing work of other team members    2. BioBrain Composition Toolset  Team Size : 10  Role : Lead developer  Technology used : WPF, C#, SQL Server, Powershell  Architecture : MVVM   Framework : .NET Framework 4.6  Duration : April 2021 - September 2022  Synopsis :   This application is a WPF based development tool used by various teams within Sartorius (a leading global supplier of bio-medical products) to develop custom software for various bio-reactors manufactured by the company.    Responsibilities :   Understanding a large legacy codebase and complex domain to takeover development from onshore teams  Co-ordinating with various teams in Germany, UK and India  Application development lead in India  Assigning and reviewing work of other team members    3. CenturyLink Billing Application  Team Size : 5  Role : UI Development Lead  Technology used : ASP.NET Core with C#, LINQ, EF Core  Architecture : 3-Layer architecture   Framework : .NET Core 3.0   Duration : Jan 2020 - April 2021  Synopsis :   A multi user application for managing the resources, timesheets and billing of Centurylink employees and contractors  Responsibilities :   UI development lead  Assigning and reviewing work of other team members    4. Phoenix Document Management System  Client : SelecTransportation, USA  Team Size : 10+  Role : UI Development Lead  Technology used : WPF with C#, LINQ, WCF, SQL Server  Architecture : MVVM architecture   Framework : .NET 4.5 , MVVM Light Framework  Other Tools used : Git with VSTS  Duration : Nov 2016 - Dec 2019  Synopsis :   A multi module, multi user system for managing the sales, inventory and accounts of one of the largest truck dealerships in the US.  Responsibilities :     UI development lead  Analyze a huge production code base to design, document and develop new features  Fix existing production issues  Assigning and reviewing work of other team members    5. Globeracer Cinematic Cycling  Client : Globeracer, Norway  Team Size : 3  Role : Development Lead  Technology used : WPF with C#, LINQ, XML, Web API, JSON  Architecture : MVVM pattern using Test Driven Development approach  Framework : .NET 4.5 , MVVM Light Framework  Other Tools used : Expression Blend, Expression Design, Git  Duration : Jan 2015 - Nov 2016  Synopsis :   A rich GUI, Windows 7 touch screen based, real-time performance monitoring and analysis system for a Norwegian indoor cycling studio, using data from custom made heart rate sensors.    Responsibilities :   Analyzed client requirements using the provided documents.  Designed UI using Blend and Visual Studio,  Developed various custom controls for the performance dials, heart-rate graphs etc.  Developed a class library for reading the unstructured JSON data and translating it to CLR objects.  Developed a custom calendar control for showing upcoming workout sessions.  Applied the SOLID principles while coding,  Wrote unit tests using Nunit and Moq  Assigned tasks to the other team members
